• a dose calculation module software (530) capable of computing the 3D delivered dose distributions (350, S341) in said description of the target based on said reconstructed delivered fluence distributions (320), on a dose algorithm (340) and on said description of the target (330).

The device according to claim 9 characterized in that said processing means is further capable of carrying out the steps of:
f. providing a detector model (400) for said electronic 2-D detectors;
g. computing 2D detector responses (420, S411) based on said reconstructed delivered photon fluence (320), on said detector model (400), and on a response calculation algorithm (410);
h. comparing said computed 2D detector responses (420, S430) to said detector responses (310) measured when irradiating with said radiation therapy apparatus having said set of machine parameters (250);
i. providing new values for said set of machine parameters (250) and reconstructing the delivered photon fluence (320, 450) by incorporating possible errors (S431) in said reconstruction;
j. repeating steps f) to i) until the value difference between said computed 2D detector responses (420) and the measured 2D detector response (310) minimizes a scoring function.

